label.value: Non-Valve Cardiac Conduit Tissue

value.value: Tissue derived from a cardiac outflow tract from which the valve structure is rendered nonfunctional, or a segment of cardiac conduit.

label.value: Minisatellite Repeat

value.value: Tandem arrays of moderately repetitive (5-50 repeats) short (10-60 bases) DNA sequences found dispersed throughout the genome and clustered near telomeres.  Their degree of repetition is two to several hundred at each locus.  Loci number in the thousands but each locus shows a distinctive repeat unit.

label.value: Ocular Tissue

value.value: Different types of tissues from the human eye.

label.value: Placenta Tissue without Amniotic Elements

value.value: The placenta and tissue derived from the placenta (other than amniotic membrane).

label.value: PF24 Plasma

value.value: The fluid portion of one unit of human blood intended for transfusion which has been separated from whole blood and placed at -18 degrees C or colder within 24 hours from whole blood collection. When prepared by automated apheresis the product is stored at 1 degree to 6 degrees C within 8 hours of collection and frozen at -18 degrees C or colder within 24 hours of collection.

label.value: PF24RT24 Plasma

value.value: Plasma Frozen within 24 Hours after Phlebotomy held at Room Temperature Up To 24 Hours after Phlebotomy (PF24RT24). Plasma prepared from automated apheresis collections can be held at room temperature for up 24 hours after collection and then frozen at -18 degrees C or colder.

label.value: Recovered Plasma

value.value: Plasma that has been collected from whole blood and is intended for further manufacture.

label.value: Plasma, Cryoprecipitated Reduced

value.value: Plasma from which cryoprecipitated antihemophilic factor (AHF) has been removed.

label.value: Single Donor Plasma

value.value: Single donor plasma separated from red donor cells within 26 days after phlebotomy (40 days when citrate phosphate dextrose adenine (CPDA-1) is used as the anticoagulant) and stored at 1-6 degrees C.

label.value: Source Plasma

value.value: Plasma collected by apheresis and is intended for further manufacturing to prepare plasma derivatives.

label.value: Therapeutic Exchange Plasma

value.value: Plasma obtained from a patient who undergoes plasma exchange (also called therapeutic plasmapheresis).

label.value: Extended Dating Platelets

value.value: Platelets that have been tested for bacteria using an FDA-cleared rapid bacterial detection device labeled as a safety measure, following testing with a growth-based quality control test cleared by the FDA for platelet components, that can support extending the expiration date of platelets past 5 days.

label.value: Origin of Replication

value.value: A DNA sequence necessary and sufficient for initiation of DNA replication.

label.value: Washed Platelets

value.value: Whole blood derived or apheresis collected platelets washed with normal saline or saline-buffered with acid citrate dextrose formula-A (ACD-A) or citrate using manual or automated methods. The washed platelets are stored at 20-24 degrees C for up to 4 hours.

label.value: Deglycerolized Red Blood Cells

value.value: Red blood cells washed free of the glycerol in which they have been stored.

label.value: Frozen Red Blood Cells

value.value: Red blood cells stored at an ultra-low temperature in the presence of a cryoprotective agent. These may be preserved for long periods of time.

label.value: Rejuvenated Frozen Red Blood Cells

value.value: Red blood cells treated with a rejuvenating solution, then frozen and stored at ultra-low temperatures in the presence of a cryoprotective agent.

label.value: Reconstituted Red Blood Cells

value.value: Red blood cells to which plasma is added to prepare a whole blood product, often with a designated specific hematocrit.

label.value: Rejuvenated, Frozen, Deglycerolized Red Blood Cells

value.value: Red blood cells treated with a rejuvenating solution, then frozen using a cryoprotective agent, and finally, washed free of the rejuvenating solution and glycerol.

label.value: Rejuvenated Red Blood Cells

value.value: Red blood cells treated to restore cell integrity with a rejuvenating solution, such as pyruvate inosine.

label.value: Washed Red Blood Cells

value.value: Red blood cells typically washed using normal saline with or without small amounts of dextrose using manual or automated methods. The washed red blood cells are stored at 1-6 degrees C for up to 24 hours.

label.value: U.S. Military Ownership

value.value: Operated by the U.S. Military and receives federal government funding.

label.value: Iodinated Polyethylene Glycol-based Hydrogel Tissue Marker

value.value: A radiopaque hydrogel containing cross-linked, iodinated polyethylene glycol (PEG) particles in a viscous carrier, with potential use as a contrast agent to enhance marking of soft tissue during a surgical procedure and concomitant radiotherapy upon computed tomography (CT), magnetic resonance (MR) and ultrasound imaging. Upon intratumoral injection, iodinated PEG-based hydrogel tissue marker localizes to and is maintained in soft tissue. Upon MR, ultrasound and/or CT imaging, the visualization of the tumor tissue is enhanced, which can facilitate tumor removal and image-guided radiotherapeutic treatment. The hydrogel particles are stable and visible through 3 months, after which they liquefy, and are absorbed by the body and cleared in the urine.

label.value: PA700 Regulatory Module

value.value: Ubiquitinated proteins are degraded by a 26S ATP-dependent protease complex, composed of a 20S catalytic proteasome and two 19S PA700 regulatory modules.  The multi-subunit PA700 complex binds two sites of the 20S proteasome and is composed of at least six related ATPases and approximately fifteen non-ATPase polypeptides.  Each of the ATPases, PSMC1-6, contains an AAA (ATPases associated with diverse cellular activities) domain.  A protein complex containing p42 and p50 enhances PA700 activation of the proteasome.

label.value: Human Cells, Tissues, and Cellular and Tissue-Based Products from Blood Vessel Tissue

value.value: Human Cells, Tissues, and Cellular and Tissue-Based Products (HCT/Ps) from the human circulatory or vascular system.

label.value: Digestive System Cancer TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of digestive system cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Human Cells, Tissues, and Cellular and Tissue-Based Products from Cardiac Tissue

value.value: Human Cells, Tissues, and Cellular and Tissue-Based Products (HCT/Ps) from the human heart.

label.value: Upper Gastrointestinal Tract Cancer TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of upper gastrointestinal tract cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Human Cells, Tissues, and Cellular and Tissue-Based Products from Musculoskeletal Tissue

value.value: Human Cells, Tissues, and Cellular and Tissue-Based Products (HCT/Ps) from the human muscular and skeletal system.

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. This staging system applies to carcinomas including squamous cell carcinoma, adenocarcinoma, adenosquamous carcinoma, undifferentiated carcinoma, neuroendocrine cancers, and adenocarcinoma with neuroendocrine features. Sarcomas, nonepithelial cancers, and gastrointestinal stromal tumors are not staged using this staging system. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Germinal Center

value.value: Sites in secondary lymphoid tissue where follicular dendritic cells present antigens to B-cells and follicular helper T-cells.

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer pTX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer pTis TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer with a finding of high-grade dysplasia, defined as malignant cells confined to the epithelium by the basement membrane. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer with tumor invading the lamina propria, muscularis mucosae, or submucosa. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer pT1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer with tumor invading the lamina propria or muscularis mucosae. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer pT1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer with tumor invading the submucosa. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Microsatellite Repeat

value.value: A variety of simple di-, tri-, tetra-, and pentanucleotide tandem repeats that are dispersed in the euchromatic arms of most chromosomes.

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer with tumor invading the muscularis propria. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer with tumor invading adventitia. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer with tumor invading adjacent structures. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Esophagus and Esophagogastric Junction Cancer pT4a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Esophagus and esophagogastric junction cancer with tumor invading the pleura, pericardium, azygos vein, diaphragm, or peritoneum. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
